<p>Unfortunately, K-12 math today is not too different from where it was 10 years ago. So a map of knowledge here has limited utility compared to domains that are rapidly changing like software engineering, where the canonical way of doing something today is often radically different than 10 years ago.</p>

<p>Another drawback of this map is that it only links to first party content. Sal Khan is an amazing educator, but is he better than the rest of the Internet combined?</p>

<p><em>Open Source Society University</em></p>

<p>Addressing exactly the above two is OSSU â€“ most well known for their <a href="https://github.com/ossu/computer-science">open source computer science curriculum</a>, which works exactly like the name says: itâ€™s a github read.me describing a computer science syllabus, where all the content linked is freely accessible.</p>

